WEBVTT

00:01.102 --> 00:01.269
.

00:01.302 --> 00:02.203
- In the criminal justice
system,

00:02.836 --> 00:03.837
sexually based offenses

00:03.871 --> 00:06.340
are considered
especially heinous.

00:06.374 --> 00:08.542
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:08.576 --> 00:10.378
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:10.411 --> 00:12.113
are members of an elite squad

00:12.146 --> 00:14.048
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:14.082 --> 00:16.384
These are their stories.

00:19.420 --> 00:21.455
[line trills]
- Hi. You've reached Nicole.

00:21.489 --> 00:23.457
Please leave a message
after the tone. Thanks.

00:23.491 --> 00:26.427
[line beeps]
- Mom, it's me again.

00:26.460 --> 00:28.329
Where are you?

00:28.362 --> 00:31.432
I keep calling and calling.

00:31.465 --> 00:34.802
Dad and I got in a fight.

00:34.835 --> 00:36.570
I'm almost home.

00:36.604 --> 00:39.573
Why aren't you picking up?

00:43.577 --> 00:45.246
Thank you.

00:56.390 --> 00:57.425
Mom?

00:57.458 --> 00:59.560
[glass shatters]

00:59.593 --> 01:01.562
[woman cries out]

01:05.499 --> 01:07.435
[woman cries out]

01:07.468 --> 01:09.470
[phone beeps three times]

01:15.576 --> 01:17.178
[woman cries out]

01:18.446 --> 01:21.415
[suspenseful music]

01:21.449 --> 01:25.553
*

01:25.586 --> 01:28.556
[dark music]

01:28.589 --> 01:29.557
*

01:29.590 --> 01:32.560
[gun loading]

01:32.593 --> 01:35.629
[woman moaning]

01:45.939 --> 01:47.375
[woman cries out]

01:51.445 --> 01:54.482
[woman moaning]

02:01.722 --> 02:05.125
[moaning and grunting]

02:07.561 --> 02:09.297
[breathing heavily]

02:09.330 --> 02:12.633
Help! He's raping me!

02:12.666 --> 02:14.468
[gunshot]

02:14.502 --> 02:15.303
[siren wails]

02:15.336 --> 02:17.238
- Detective Perry, Homicide?
- Yeah.

02:17.271 --> 02:18.439
Lieutenant Benson, SVU.

02:18.472 --> 02:19.740
- Thanks for getting here
so fast.

02:19.773 --> 02:21.209
- So, what we looking at?

02:21.242 --> 02:23.377
- DOA is Trey Franklin, 15.

02:23.411 --> 02:25.279
Rifle shot to the head,
close range.

02:25.313 --> 02:27.681
- You said the shooter
interrupted a rape?

02:27.715 --> 02:29.583
- Yeah. Luke Keller, also 15.

02:29.617 --> 02:32.620
Saw Franklin assaulting
his mother, Nicole Keller--

02:32.653 --> 02:34.622
Dr. Nicole Keller, 45.

02:34.655 --> 02:35.589
- Did you keep them separated?

02:35.623 --> 02:37.391
- Yep. We secured the scene
and the weapon,

02:37.425 --> 02:38.359
took the kid's
initial statements.

02:38.392 --> 02:40.294
He's upstairs.
The mother's in the living room.

02:40.328 --> 02:41.562
- Okay, so we'll take
the disclosure.

02:41.595 --> 02:42.696
- That's why I called you guys.

02:42.730 --> 02:44.565
- All right.
Rollins, you're with me.

02:44.598 --> 02:45.933
Fin, Carisi.

02:45.966 --> 02:47.668
- We'll take the son.

02:49.270 --> 02:52.306
- Luke, I'm Detective Carisi.
This is Detective Tutuola.

02:52.340 --> 02:53.574
- I already told
the other police.

02:53.607 --> 02:55.409
I had to do it.
He was raping my mom.

02:55.443 --> 02:58.412
- Okay, just breathe. We just
want to know what happened.

02:58.446 --> 03:00.681
- I was supposed
to spend the night at my dad's,

03:00.714 --> 03:02.716
but we got in a fight,
so I came home.

03:02.750 --> 03:06.454
- What time did you leave?
- I left my dad's about 9:00.

03:06.487 --> 03:08.289
I really wanted
to talk to my mom.

03:08.322 --> 03:10.224
I tried calling.
She wasn't answering.

03:10.258 --> 03:12.293
- Luke, now, did your mother
have plans tonight?

03:12.326 --> 03:14.562
- Staying home, doing paperwork.

03:14.595 --> 03:15.729
She's a psychiatrist.

03:15.763 --> 03:17.331
- What time did you get home?

03:17.365 --> 03:18.566
- About 10:00. It was dark.

03:18.599 --> 03:21.435
I heard a noise downstairs,
thought someone was breaking in,

03:21.469 --> 03:24.572
so I called 911, and then went
to the closet to get my rifle.

03:24.605 --> 03:26.574
- Your rifle?

03:26.607 --> 03:28.342
- Yeah.
My dad gave it to me.

03:28.376 --> 03:29.443
He likes to go hunting.

03:29.477 --> 03:31.579
- Then what happened?
- I walked into the kitchen,

03:31.612 --> 03:33.581
and he was attacking my mom.

03:33.614 --> 03:35.516
- What did you see?
- She was staring at me.

03:35.549 --> 03:38.719
She was so scared. Then she
screamed "Help! He's raping me!"

03:38.752 --> 03:40.621
so I pulled the trigger.

03:40.654 --> 03:42.590
I didn't think I was
actually gonna hit him.

03:42.623 --> 03:43.691
[sobs]

03:43.724 --> 03:44.792
- I have to see my son.

03:44.825 --> 03:46.594
He can't handle this stress.

03:46.627 --> 03:47.595
He's got a lot
of generalized anxiety.

03:47.628 --> 03:49.630
- And I understand that,
but right now we need

03:49.663 --> 03:50.831
to speak to both of you
separately.

03:50.864 --> 03:52.766
- Right. Okay.

03:52.800 --> 03:54.335
- Okay.
- I understand.

03:54.368 --> 03:56.470
- So, Dr. Keller,
I need to know

03:56.504 --> 03:58.739
exactly what happened

03:58.772 --> 04:00.474
from your perspective.

04:00.508 --> 04:03.311
- Okay. Um, right.

04:03.344 --> 04:05.613
I was in the kitchen.

04:05.646 --> 04:07.481
I was--I was getting some wine.

04:07.515 --> 04:10.484
And he--I was there,
and I turn around,

04:10.518 --> 04:11.785
and--and he was right there.

04:11.819 --> 04:13.754
And I tried to get away.

04:13.787 --> 04:16.657
I did. I tried.
And he--he overpowered me.

04:16.690 --> 04:19.293
- Was this a break-in?
Or maybe he followed you home?

04:19.327 --> 04:21.429
- No. No. I let him in.

04:23.831 --> 04:25.466
- You let him in?

04:25.499 --> 04:27.635
So you knew him?

04:27.668 --> 04:29.303
- Yes.

04:29.337 --> 04:31.372
He was my son's best friend.

04:31.405 --> 04:38.446
*

04:39.447 --> 04:42.416
[dramatic music]

05:26.494 --> 05:27.227
- The mother let him in
voluntarily.

05:28.061 --> 05:30.864
She said he was
the son's best friend.

05:30.898 --> 05:33.401
- Explains why there's no signs
of forced entry.

05:34.902 --> 05:37.104
- Okay, if Luke wasn't home,
why did she let him in?

05:37.137 --> 05:39.973
- [sighs] He asked to come in
to do his homework.

05:40.007 --> 05:42.042
Apparently he's been having
a rough time at home.

05:42.075 --> 05:43.444
- So, he just hung out
in the house

05:43.477 --> 05:44.478
while she was upstairs working?

05:44.512 --> 05:46.013
- That's what she said.

05:46.046 --> 05:48.048
- Okay, so, Luke walks in
unexpectedly,

05:48.081 --> 05:50.083
hears his mother screaming
that she's being raped,

05:50.117 --> 05:52.119
and he fires.

05:52.152 --> 05:54.422
We're not thinking
premeditation at all?

05:54.455 --> 05:55.989
- He called 911.

05:56.023 --> 05:58.426
The rifle was locked up.
Registered to his father,

05:58.459 --> 05:59.993
so technically not legal,

06:00.027 --> 06:02.796
but the shooting still sounds
justifiable to me.

06:02.830 --> 06:04.465
But I'm a cop, not a prosecutor.

06:04.498 --> 06:09.136
- Okay, what about the DOA?
I mean, Trey Franklin's parents.

06:09.169 --> 06:11.439
- On their way
to the ME's office.

06:11.472 --> 06:13.407
How about if I meet
one of your guys over there?

06:13.441 --> 06:15.075
- Good idea.
Thanks.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.180
Is it okay if we pick up
where we left off?

06:20.213 --> 06:22.015
- Yeah. Sure.

06:22.049 --> 06:24.518
- Dr. Keller,
you said that you knew

06:24.552 --> 06:26.153
that you shouldn't have
let Trey in.

06:26.186 --> 06:28.822
- I had an instinct.
Something was wrong.

06:28.856 --> 06:33.126
The way he looked at me,
you know? Made me uneasy.

06:33.160 --> 06:35.529
- But you were okay with him
being friends with your son?

06:35.563 --> 06:38.131
- Yes. I didn't want
to shut Trey out.

06:38.165 --> 06:39.500
I felt badly for him.

06:39.533 --> 06:42.169
His family life was
very unstable.

06:42.202 --> 06:45.906
- So, Trey came to your door
at what time?

06:45.939 --> 06:48.442
- Uh, it was around 9:00.

06:48.476 --> 06:50.143
Nine o'clock.

06:50.177 --> 06:53.180
Uh, I put my work away
for the night.

06:53.213 --> 06:56.183
And he asked where Luke was,

06:56.216 --> 06:57.518
said they were supposed
to study.

06:57.551 --> 06:59.487
And I said,
"There must be a mix-up,

06:59.520 --> 07:02.055
'cause Luke's at his father's
house in Westport."

07:02.089 --> 07:06.794
- Okay. Go on.

07:06.827 --> 07:10.464
- Then he asked if he could--
if he could come in anyway,

07:10.498 --> 07:11.632
do his homework.

07:11.665 --> 07:13.200
And...[sighs]

07:13.233 --> 07:14.602
I said yes.

07:14.635 --> 07:16.937
And then I went upstairs
to get ready for bed.

07:16.970 --> 07:18.806
- So, that's when you changed
into your nightgown?

07:18.839 --> 07:20.140
- No. I already had
my nightgown on,

07:20.173 --> 07:22.175
and I'd already started
getting ready for bed

07:22.209 --> 07:23.243
when he rang the doorbell.

07:23.276 --> 07:24.845
- Okay, so,
you answered the door

07:24.878 --> 07:27.548
in your nightgown,
and then you went back upstairs.

07:27.581 --> 07:31.084
- Yes. I-I went upstairs
for about an hour.

07:31.118 --> 07:33.253
It started getting late,

07:33.286 --> 07:36.557
so I-I went back downstairs

07:36.590 --> 07:40.628
and I told Trey--I told him
it was time to go home.

07:40.661 --> 07:44.097
- So, during that time,
your son was calling you.

07:44.131 --> 07:47.200
Um, why didn't you pick up?

07:47.234 --> 07:50.571
- No, I didn't get the message.
I didn't get any messages.

07:50.604 --> 07:53.273
I--when I work sometimes
I don't even look at my phone,

07:53.306 --> 07:54.207
and Luke was with his dad.

07:54.241 --> 07:56.109
- Right, but you weren't
working then, right?

07:56.143 --> 07:59.980
Because he started to call
I think at 9:30 to 10:00, right?

08:00.013 --> 08:02.182
You had already put your work
down for the night?

08:02.215 --> 08:05.152
- Right. Yes, I had. I went
downstairs for a glass of wine.

08:05.185 --> 08:06.319
- Oh.
- Okay? To relax.

08:06.353 --> 08:11.992
And that's when I felt him--
I felt his presence behind me,

08:12.025 --> 08:13.994
and I turned around,
and it was Trey.

08:14.027 --> 08:14.995
He was right there.

08:15.028 --> 08:16.564
And he put his hands on me.

08:16.597 --> 08:19.266
- So, what did you do?
- I tried to stop it.

08:19.299 --> 08:21.569
I tried to tell him
I understood.

08:21.602 --> 08:25.305
I understood sexual impulses
and urges.

08:25.338 --> 08:26.874
Believe me.
I'm a psychiatrist.

08:26.907 --> 08:29.543
I've dealt with this issue
many, many times.

08:29.577 --> 08:31.645
But he...

08:31.679 --> 08:35.949
put me up against
the kitchen counter, and...

08:35.983 --> 08:38.185
he lifted up my nightgown.

08:39.653 --> 08:41.655
- Okay.
Take your time.

08:44.124 --> 08:47.160
- I, uh...
[stammering]

08:50.664 --> 08:52.199
He forced himself inside me,

08:52.232 --> 08:54.101
and, um,

08:54.134 --> 08:56.036
I-I tried to scream,

08:56.069 --> 08:58.138
and he put his hand on my mouth.

08:58.171 --> 09:01.308
And I--[sobs]
There was a kitchen knife,

09:01.341 --> 09:05.579
and I tried to reach it,
but it was too far away.

09:05.613 --> 09:08.582
So I just closed my eyes,
and I tried to survive.

09:08.616 --> 09:11.318
And I thought about my son.

09:11.351 --> 09:12.586
I thought about Luke,

09:12.620 --> 09:16.657
and I needed to stay alive
for him.

09:16.690 --> 09:18.358
And then--and then I looked up,
and he was there,

09:18.391 --> 09:21.028
and I yelled help: "Help!"

09:21.061 --> 09:23.597
- Mm. Mm-hmm.

09:23.631 --> 09:25.098
- And then I heard the gunshot.

09:25.132 --> 09:28.636
- So, Mrs. Keller,
did you know that your son

09:28.669 --> 09:29.637
had a rifle in the house?

09:29.670 --> 09:33.641
- Yes. In a locked safe. Yes.

09:33.674 --> 09:35.943
It was a gift--it was a gift
from his father.

09:35.976 --> 09:37.077
He's a hunter.

09:37.110 --> 09:38.746
- Okay. Is Luke a hunter, too?

09:38.779 --> 09:42.716
- No. He--he's so sensitive.

09:45.218 --> 09:47.688
He actually hated the idea
of having a gun in the house.

09:47.721 --> 09:50.691
Hated it.

09:50.724 --> 09:56.229
He went hunting, and there was
a deer in his sight,

09:56.263 --> 09:58.265
and he couldn't even
pull the trigger.

10:01.669 --> 10:05.072
I--

10:05.105 --> 10:06.640
it doesn't--

10:06.674 --> 10:08.108
it doesn't make sense.

10:08.141 --> 10:10.277
It--it doesn't make sense.

10:10.310 --> 10:14.414
That's why it's so--

10:14.447 --> 10:17.651
I want to see him.

10:17.685 --> 10:20.120
- Is my mom gonna be okay?

10:20.153 --> 10:22.222
- Yeah.
Yeah, she's at the hospital.

10:22.255 --> 10:24.758
She's--she's getting
checked out now. Come on.

10:24.792 --> 10:27.327
I know what you went through.

10:27.360 --> 10:29.262
I know it's tough,
all right?

10:29.296 --> 10:31.064
Have a seat.

10:31.098 --> 10:33.801
But we need to go over it again,
step by step.

10:33.834 --> 10:35.402
Can you do that?

10:35.435 --> 10:37.170
- Think so.

10:37.204 --> 10:38.305
- Okay.

10:38.338 --> 10:40.207
So, you said you walked
into your house,

10:40.240 --> 10:41.742
you heard noises,
you called 911,

10:41.775 --> 10:43.343
you grabbed your rifle,

10:43.376 --> 10:45.245
walked down to the kitchen,
right?

10:45.278 --> 10:47.114
- Mm-hmm.
- Okay, Luke.

10:47.147 --> 10:49.783
Before you fired, did you say
"stop" or "get off of her,"

10:49.817 --> 10:51.018
or anything like that?

10:51.051 --> 10:52.720
- I don't think so.

10:52.753 --> 10:54.855
I just reacted.

10:54.888 --> 10:57.858
- When did you realize
it was Trey?

10:57.891 --> 10:59.459
- Not until after.

10:59.492 --> 11:02.429
I thought it was just some man
who broke in, not Trey.

11:02.462 --> 11:04.264
- How well did you guys
know each other?

11:04.297 --> 11:07.067
- We're best friends.

11:09.202 --> 11:10.804
We were.

11:13.774 --> 11:15.776
I killed my best friend.

11:15.809 --> 11:17.310
- Okay.
We're gonna take a break.

11:17.344 --> 11:19.112
We'll get you some water.

11:19.146 --> 11:21.314
- Luke's dad is here.

11:21.348 --> 11:23.350
- Luke, you all right?

11:23.383 --> 11:25.152
- [crying] Dad!

11:25.185 --> 11:27.487
- Hey, hey, hey.
- He was hurting Mom. I swear.

11:27.520 --> 11:29.757
- It's okay. It's okay.
I'm here now.

11:32.492 --> 11:35.062
Uh, do I need a lawyer?

11:35.095 --> 11:37.464
- We're still investigating,
but it seems like Luke fired

11:37.497 --> 11:40.200
to save his mother
from a sexual assault.

11:40.233 --> 11:42.135
That being said,
these cases can get tricky.

11:42.169 --> 11:43.804
- Appreciate your honesty.
We're done talking.

11:43.837 --> 11:45.806
- It's all right, buddy.
Come here.

11:45.839 --> 11:47.340
It's all right.

11:47.374 --> 11:49.877
Everything's gonna be okay,
all right?

11:53.881 --> 11:56.083
- Yeah, that's his bracelet.

11:56.116 --> 11:59.352
And the scar.
He burnt his hand

11:59.386 --> 12:01.121
on a camping trip
when he was ten.

12:01.154 --> 12:03.891
- [crying] I want to see him.
I want to see my son's body.

12:03.924 --> 12:05.492
- Mrs. Franklin, ma'am.

12:05.525 --> 12:08.195
It's better that you don't.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.863
- I still don't understand
what happened.

12:09.897 --> 12:12.766
- A classmate of his,
Luke Keller,

12:12.800 --> 12:13.934
he fired a weapon.

12:13.967 --> 12:15.468
The bullet struck
and killed him.

12:15.502 --> 12:18.438
- Luke?
That doesn't make any sense.

12:18.471 --> 12:20.507
They're--they're friends.
- Was it an accident?

12:20.540 --> 12:22.242
- We're still looking into it.

12:22.275 --> 12:26.246
But Luke's mother says your son
was sexually assaulting her.

12:26.279 --> 12:27.848
- What?

12:27.881 --> 12:29.349
And that's why Luke shot him?

12:29.382 --> 12:30.517
- It's possible.

12:30.550 --> 12:34.121
- No. No. It's not possible!

12:34.154 --> 12:36.824
Trey would never assault anyone.
Ever.

12:36.857 --> 12:38.558
- You may be right.
It's obviously very early

12:38.591 --> 12:39.893
in the investigation.

12:39.927 --> 12:41.494
- Is Luke under arrest?

12:41.528 --> 12:44.297
- Not yet.
- Oh, I see.

12:44.331 --> 12:46.867
White kid shoots black kid,
got to be the black kid's fault.

12:46.900 --> 12:48.168
That's what you're saying?

12:48.201 --> 12:49.502
- No. Not even close.

12:49.536 --> 12:51.805
We're just trying to figure out
what happened.

12:51.839 --> 12:54.274
- Yeah, well, me too,

12:54.307 --> 12:57.544
'cause my son was a good kid.

12:57.577 --> 13:01.548
No. A great kid.

13:01.581 --> 13:05.385
- I want to see my son. Now.

13:06.619 --> 13:08.288
- Okay.

13:12.860 --> 13:17.564
*

13:17.597 --> 13:18.966
[knocks on glass]

13:20.267 --> 13:27.307
*

13:42.522 --> 13:44.224
- What do we know
about Trey Franklin?

13:44.257 --> 13:47.594
- Only son of Charles
and Regina Franklin.

13:47.627 --> 13:50.630
Father's an English professor.
Mother is an oncology nurse.

13:50.663 --> 13:52.599
No priors. Good student.

13:52.632 --> 13:54.902
He started high school
at Manor Hill in September.

13:54.935 --> 13:56.904
- Rape kit?
- There's no semen.

13:56.937 --> 13:58.939
Just a few minor abrasions.

13:58.972 --> 14:00.640
- How long did the mother
know Trey?

14:00.673 --> 14:02.409
- A few months.
She said she didn't mind

14:02.442 --> 14:03.610
her son being friends with Trey,

14:03.643 --> 14:05.946
but she had a bad feeling
about him from the beginning,

14:05.979 --> 14:07.347
whatever that means.

14:07.380 --> 14:08.648
- Because he's black?

14:08.681 --> 14:11.384
- No. I didn't get a sense
that it was racial.

14:11.418 --> 14:13.553
- And Luke.
Do you believe his story?

14:13.586 --> 14:15.355
- I do.
He's taking this hard.

14:15.388 --> 14:17.657
He had no clue the alleged
rapist was his friend.

14:17.690 --> 14:20.961
- But firing the rifle was the
only way to stop the assault?

14:20.994 --> 14:22.629
- He panicked.
He was trying to scare

14:22.662 --> 14:23.663
whoever he thought it was away.

14:23.696 --> 14:27.234
- Okay, so they were friends.
Any recent problems?

14:27.267 --> 14:28.936
- Not that we can find.

14:28.969 --> 14:30.403
- So, Trey came over
to study with Luke,

14:30.437 --> 14:31.972
but Luke wasn't there.

14:32.005 --> 14:33.974
If Trey knew
that Luke wasn't gonna be home,

14:34.007 --> 14:35.542
that would help to establish
his mindset.

14:35.575 --> 14:39.312
Then he went to Nicole's house
knowing she was gonna be alone.

14:39.346 --> 14:40.981
- But we already checked
Luke's phone.

14:41.014 --> 14:43.450
There's no texts or emails
between him and Trey.

14:43.483 --> 14:45.652
- Okay, so let's dig in
to their social media account,

14:45.685 --> 14:47.687
talk to the friends,
see if we can find anything out.

14:47.720 --> 14:50.090
- We should search his locker
